WEBVTT

00:07.975 --> 00:09.643
* IT'S A RARE CONDITION *

00:09.710 --> 00:11.279
* IN THIS DAY AND AGE *

00:11.345 --> 00:14.648
* TO READ ANY GOOD NEWS
ON THE NEWSPAPER PAGE *

00:14.715 --> 00:18.652
* AND LOVE AND TRADITION
OF THE GRAND DESIGN *

00:18.719 --> 00:23.224
* SOME PEOPLE SAY
IS EVEN HARDER TO FIND *

00:23.291 --> 00:26.360
* WELL, THEN, THERE MUST BE
SOME MAGIC CLUE *

00:26.427 --> 00:30.664
* INSIDE THESE
GENTLE WALLS *

00:30.731 --> 00:33.734
* 'CAUSE ALL I SEE
IS A TOWER OF DREAMS *

00:33.801 --> 00:38.772
* REAL LOVE BURSTIN'
OUT OF EVERY SEAM *

00:38.839 --> 00:42.310
* AS DAYS GO BY *

00:42.376 --> 00:45.913
* WE'RE GONNA FILL OUR
HOUSE WITH HAPPINESS *

00:45.979 --> 00:48.449
* THE MOON MAY CRY *

00:48.516 --> 00:52.720
* WE'RE GONNA SMOTHER
THE BLUES WITH TENDERNESS *

00:52.786 --> 00:55.689
* AS DAYS GO BY *

00:55.756 --> 00:59.093
* THERE'S ROOM FOR
YOU ROOM FOR ME *

00:59.160 --> 01:03.964
* FOR GENTLE HEARTS
AN OPPORTUNITY *

01:04.031 --> 01:06.400
* AS DAYS GO BY *

01:06.467 --> 01:13.341
* IT'S THE BIGGER
LOVE OF THE FAMILY *

01:23.351 --> 01:26.154
GOOD NIGHT.
COME AGAIN.

01:36.230 --> 01:38.566
STEVE.

01:38.632 --> 01:40.268
STEVE, ARE YOU HERE?

01:41.034 --> 01:42.436
WHAT'S GOING ON,
LAURA?

01:42.503 --> 01:45.873
THIS WAS ON A TABLE
THAT WAS EMPTY
A SECOND AGO.

01:45.939 --> 01:49.643
"FAREWELL, MY LAURA.
BY STEVEN Q. URKEL."

01:49.710 --> 01:51.445
THIS MUST BE HIS ENTRY

01:51.512 --> 01:53.547
IN THE SHORT-STORY
CONTEST.

01:53.614 --> 01:55.416
YEAH. HE'S DELIBERATELY
BEING MYSTERIOUS

01:55.483 --> 01:58.986
TO MAKE ME WANT
TO READ IT. WELL...

01:59.052 --> 02:00.254
IT WORKED.

02:03.524 --> 02:06.760
[STEVE]
IT ALL STARTED
ON A TUESDAY.

02:06.827 --> 02:09.197
[SAXOPHONE PLAYING]

02:09.263 --> 02:11.532
AN ORDINARY TUESDAY,

02:11.599 --> 02:15.135
THE KIND THAT FALLS BETWEEN
MONDAY AND WEDNESDAY.

02:16.370 --> 02:19.139
YEP, ANY WAY
YOU LOOK AT IT,

02:19.207 --> 02:20.841
IT WAS TUESDAY.

02:25.513 --> 02:26.347
HEY, MAX.

02:26.414 --> 02:29.617
PUT A SOCK IN THE SAX.

02:32.052 --> 02:34.288
ALLOW ME
TO INTRODUCE MYSELF.

02:34.355 --> 02:35.923
THE NAME IS DANGER...

02:35.989 --> 02:37.891
JOHNNY DANGER.

02:37.958 --> 02:39.660
FORMER RANGER.

02:39.727 --> 02:40.761
AND EVEN STRANGER,

02:40.828 --> 02:44.198
MY COUSIN
IS STEWART GRANGER.

02:48.469 --> 02:50.538
I'M A PRIVATE
INVESTIGATOR--

02:50.604 --> 02:54.107
A P.I., A SHAMUS,
A SLEUTH, A GUMSHOE.

02:54.174 --> 02:56.710
THINGS WERE KIND OF SLOW.

02:56.777 --> 02:58.246
AND THEN...

02:59.313 --> 03:01.682
[DRUMS BEATING]

03:34.682 --> 03:35.983
I WANT TO SEE...

03:36.049 --> 03:37.985
JOHNNY DANGER.

03:39.353 --> 03:42.590
AND WHOM THE HECK
ARE YOU?

03:45.259 --> 03:47.428
LAURA WIGGLESWORTH.

03:47.495 --> 03:51.031
I'LL SEE
IF MR. DANGER IS IN.

03:51.098 --> 03:53.133
[INTERCOM BUZZES]

03:53.200 --> 03:54.668
WHAT IS IT, MAX?

03:54.735 --> 03:57.271
THERE'S
A MISS WIGGLESWORTH HERE.

03:57.338 --> 03:59.907
OH? WELL, JUST A SEC.

04:08.382 --> 04:09.983
SHOW HER IN.

04:14.855 --> 04:16.724
[DRUMS BEATING]

04:29.637 --> 04:32.706
HEY, MAX.
WE MAY BE A WHILE.

04:32.773 --> 04:34.608
TAKE A LONG LUNCH.

04:34.675 --> 04:37.678
WELL, WHEN DO YOU
WANT ME BACK?

04:38.879 --> 04:40.914
AUGUST.

04:48.422 --> 04:51.425
I'M JOHNNY DANGER.

04:52.393 --> 04:55.729
I'M LAURA WIGGLESWORTH.

04:55.796 --> 05:01.369
I SAW RIGHT AWAY THIS LAURA
WAS NO ORDINARY DAME.

05:01.435 --> 05:03.971
SILKY HAIR, SULTRY EYES.

05:04.037 --> 05:06.607
AND A PAIR OF LEGS
THAT STARTED AT HER WAIST

05:06.674 --> 05:09.410
AND WENT ALL THE WAY
TO THE GROUND.

05:25.393 --> 05:26.927
YOU WERE SAYING?

05:27.828 --> 05:30.230
I NEED YOUR HELP,
MR. DANGER.

05:30.297 --> 05:33.333
I NEED IT BAD.

05:33.401 --> 05:35.369
REAL BAD.

05:37.337 --> 05:38.839
DESPERATELY.

05:38.906 --> 05:40.374
[GASP]

05:47.114 --> 05:51.251
I'M SO FRIGHTENED.
SOMEONE IS TRYING
TO KILL MY AUNT.

05:51.318 --> 05:55.122
I SEE. WHAT'S
YOUR AUNT'S NAME?

05:55.188 --> 05:56.757
WHY WOULD ANYONE
WANT TO KILL HER?

05:56.824 --> 05:59.460
WHO DO YOU LIKE
IN THE WORLD SERIES?

05:59.527 --> 06:01.529
RACHEL CRAWFISH,
YOU GOT ME,

06:01.595 --> 06:04.732
AND I LIKE THE
ST. LOUIS CARDINALS.

06:04.798 --> 06:07.401
RACHEL CRAWFISH?
WHY WOULD ANYONE WANT
TO KILL HER?

06:07.468 --> 06:09.403
AND I LIKE THE RED SOX.

06:09.470 --> 06:11.505
THAT'S RIGHT,
I DON'T KNOW,

06:11.572 --> 06:14.107
AND I STILL
LIKE THE CARDS.

06:14.174 --> 06:16.677
SO, WHAT DO YOU SAY,

06:16.744 --> 06:18.446
WILL YOU PROTECT
MY AUNT

06:18.512 --> 06:21.515
AND BET 10 BUCKS
ON THE SERIES?

06:22.315 --> 06:23.817
YOU'RE ON...

06:23.884 --> 06:25.385
AND YOU'RE ON.

06:28.822 --> 06:30.891
GOOD. YOU START
8:00 TONIGHT

06:30.958 --> 06:34.394
AT MY AUNT'S
RESTAURANT--
RACHEL'S PLACE.

06:36.597 --> 06:38.799
DON'T BE LATE.

06:38.866 --> 06:40.000
[DRUMS BEATING]

06:40.067 --> 06:41.969
WHAT A WOMAN.

06:42.035 --> 06:44.938
GLITTER AND GLITZ
ON THE OUTSIDE,

06:45.005 --> 06:46.273
BUT ON THE INSIDE...

06:46.339 --> 06:51.679
A HINT
OF THE GIRL NEXT DOOR.

06:51.745 --> 06:54.848
BUT ONE QUESTION
KEPT NAGGING AT ME...

06:54.915 --> 06:58.452
WHERE DOES SHE HIDE
THOSE DRUMS?

07:03.123 --> 07:06.660
* I ONCE FELL IN LOVE *

07:06.727 --> 07:09.563
* WITH A GUY IN THE BAND *

07:09.630 --> 07:11.532
* THAT MAN BROKE MY HEART *

07:11.599 --> 07:14.367
* BUT HIS WIFE
BROKE MY HAND *

07:14.434 --> 07:17.771
* I'M JUST
AN UNLUCKY STAR *

07:17.838 --> 07:21.475
* AN UNLUCKY STAR *

07:21.542 --> 07:23.744
* IF YOU WANNA RIDE
TO FORTUNE *

07:23.811 --> 07:28.516
* FIND ANOTHER CAR *

07:35.789 --> 07:38.158
HELLO, LAURA.
HOW DID I SOUND?

07:38.225 --> 07:40.528
MARVELOUS, AS USUAL.

07:40.594 --> 07:42.696
RACHEL
WAS A KNOCKOUT.

07:42.763 --> 07:44.898
AND THERE WAS
SOMETHING ELSE ABOUT HER,

07:44.965 --> 07:48.636
SOMETHING I COULDN'T QUITE
PUT MY FINGER ON.

07:48.702 --> 07:52.540
WHO IS THIS SEXY MAN?

07:55.108 --> 07:56.710
THEN IT CAME TO ME.

07:56.777 --> 07:58.546
SHE HAD GOOD TASTE.

08:01.048 --> 08:02.750
THIS IS JOHNNY DANGER,

08:02.816 --> 08:04.585
THE PRIVATE EYE
I TOLD YOU ABOUT.

08:04.652 --> 08:09.289
OH. MY NIECE
SEEMS TO THINK
I NEED PROTECTION.

08:09.356 --> 08:11.992
CAN YOU PROTECT ME,
JOHNNY?

08:12.059 --> 08:13.727
ARE YOU KIDDING?

08:13.794 --> 08:16.764
WHY, MY MIDDLE NAME'S
TURTLE WAX.

08:18.198 --> 08:21.802
NOW, YOU TWO
JUST GO ABOUT YOUR
NORMAL BUSINESS

08:21.869 --> 08:24.972
WHILE I MAKE MYSELF
INCONSPICUOUS.

08:25.038 --> 08:27.207
FOR THE NEXT
SEVERAL HOURS,

08:27.274 --> 08:28.676
I CASED THE JOINT.

08:28.742 --> 08:31.912
IT WAS A HOTBED
OF SUSPICIOUS ACTIVITY.

08:32.813 --> 08:35.515
EVENING,
MRS. WIGGLESWORTH.

08:36.349 --> 08:37.317
YEAH?

08:37.384 --> 08:39.853
WHO SAYS?

08:39.920 --> 08:43.223
GEE, YOUR SISTER'S
DONE A GREAT JOB
WITH THIS PLACE.

08:43.290 --> 08:46.126
YOU THINK I COULDN'T?
THAT'S WHAT YOU'RE SAYING?

08:46.193 --> 08:48.228
NO!
YES, YOU ARE!

08:48.295 --> 08:51.932
YOU THINK I'M NOTHING,
I'M A NOBODY. BUT I'M A PERSON.

08:51.999 --> 08:56.970
I HAVE FEELINGS...
AND MY ORIGINAL NOSE.

08:57.037 --> 08:59.707
GEE, I WONDER
WHO DROPPED A SCORPION

08:59.773 --> 09:01.609
IN HER GIRDLE.

09:05.012 --> 09:06.213
HEY, MOM.

09:06.279 --> 09:09.116
WANT TO PLAY THE NUMBERS?
IT ONLY COSTS $1.00.

09:09.182 --> 09:12.185
WHO DO I LOOK LIKE?
THE BANK OF HARRIETTE?

09:15.222 --> 09:17.157
EXCUSE ME.

09:17.224 --> 09:20.493
YOU WOULDN'T HAPPEN
TO BE LAURA'S BROTHER?

09:20.560 --> 09:24.064
I HOPE SO.
I'M WEARING HIS UNDERWEAR.

09:28.168 --> 09:30.070
MR. DANGER.

09:30.137 --> 09:32.239
OFFICER WIGGLESWORTH.

09:41.381 --> 09:43.651
WHAT DO YOU WANT HERE?

09:43.717 --> 09:47.655
THE FRIED CHICKEN
AND A SIDE
OF INFORMATION.

09:48.488 --> 09:50.257
I DON'T LIKE YOU,
DANGER,

09:50.323 --> 09:53.927
BECAUSE WHEREVER YOU GO
TROUBLE IS SURE TO FOLLOW.

09:53.994 --> 09:54.962
YOU FOLLOW?

09:55.028 --> 09:56.296
I FOLLOW.

09:56.363 --> 09:59.599
REMEMBER, WE'RE
ON THE SAME SIDE
OF THE LAW.

09:59.667 --> 10:01.869
THERE'S ROOM FOR YOU
AND THERE'S ROOM FOR ME.

10:01.935 --> 10:03.771
ALTHOUGH, LET'S BE
QUITE HONEST.

10:03.837 --> 10:08.642
YOU TAKE UP
A LOT MORE ROOM
THAN ME.

10:08.709 --> 10:11.044
HEH HEH HEH.

10:11.111 --> 10:13.346
[DRUMS BEATING]

10:18.418 --> 10:19.687
LAURA!

10:21.889 --> 10:24.357
HELLO, JOHNNY.

10:24.424 --> 10:26.626
[DRUMS BEATING]

10:29.863 --> 10:31.965
CARE TO WET
YOUR WHISTLE?

10:32.032 --> 10:33.734
WHY NOT?

10:36.336 --> 10:38.605
YOU DO KNOW
HOW TO WHISTLE,
DON'T YOU?

10:38.672 --> 10:40.007
OH, SURE.

10:40.073 --> 10:43.610
YOU JUST PUT YOUR LIPS
TOGETHER AND GO...

10:43.677 --> 10:45.713
PFFT!

10:52.552 --> 10:54.321
SEE YOU LATER,
BIG BOY.

10:54.387 --> 10:56.690
[DRUMS BEATING]

11:00.260 --> 11:02.996
LAURA HAD A HALF NELSON
ON MY HEART.

11:03.063 --> 11:05.799
MY PULSE WAS RACING.
MY HEAD WAS POUNDING.

11:05.866 --> 11:07.735
THE ROOM WAS SPINNING.

11:10.137 --> 11:13.006
THEN I REALIZED...
THIS WASN'T LOVE.

11:13.073 --> 11:15.943
SOMEBODY HAD SLIPPED ME
A MICKEY!

11:18.078 --> 11:19.146
HEY, LADY!

11:19.212 --> 11:20.313
AAH! OH!

11:22.415 --> 11:24.184
AGGHH!

11:29.489 --> 11:32.125
[SNORTING]

11:36.663 --> 11:38.365
WHEN I CAME TO,

11:38.431 --> 11:40.033
I FELT LIKE ORSON WELLES

11:40.100 --> 11:43.703
HAD BEEN TAP-DANCING
ON MY HEAD.

11:44.637 --> 11:47.207
RACHEL. OH.

11:47.274 --> 11:49.409
WHAT TIME IS IT?

11:49.476 --> 11:52.479
HOW LONG
HAVE I BEEN OUT?

11:52.545 --> 11:54.114
RACHEL.

11:59.820 --> 12:01.922
EXTRA! EXTRA!
READ ALL ABOUT IT!

12:01.989 --> 12:05.425
RACHEL CRAWFISH FOUND
STABBED TO DEATH!

12:17.170 --> 12:22.075
ONE WEEK LATER,
ON A DARK AND STORMY NIGHT,

12:22.142 --> 12:25.846
I GATHERED EVERYBODY
AT THE WIGGLESWORTH HOUSE.

12:25.913 --> 12:28.348
[THUNDER]

12:32.853 --> 12:34.855
MR. DANGER,

12:34.922 --> 12:38.558
IT'S A DARK
AND STORMY NIGHT.

12:38.625 --> 12:42.996
WHY HAVE YOU
GATHERED US HERE AT
THE WIGGLESWORTH HOUSE?

12:43.063 --> 12:46.399
BECAUSE YOU ALL
HAD TWO THINGS
IN COMMON.

12:46.466 --> 12:47.767
AND WHAT'S THAT?

12:47.835 --> 12:49.837
YOU ALL KNEW
RACHEL CRAWFISH,

12:49.903 --> 12:52.105
AND YOU ALL HAD
REASON TO KILL HER.

12:56.543 --> 12:58.278
YOU'RE WAY
OFF BASE HERE.

12:58.345 --> 12:59.847
RACHEL WAS LOVED.

12:59.913 --> 13:02.082
IS THAT SO?

13:02.149 --> 13:06.686
WELL, HOW DID YOU
FEEL ABOUT RACHEL...

13:06.753 --> 13:09.356
HARRIETTE?

13:09.422 --> 13:11.691
HEY. SHE WAS MY SISTER.

13:11.758 --> 13:13.894
I, UH...

13:13.961 --> 13:16.129
SORT OF LOVED HER.

13:21.134 --> 13:23.837
YOU WERE JEALOUS
OF RACHEL.

13:23.904 --> 13:26.106
AFTER ALL, YOU
DID LOAN HER
THE MONEY

13:26.173 --> 13:28.141
TO START
RACHEL'S PLACE.

13:28.208 --> 13:32.379
BUT THEN
RACHEL BECAME
RICH AND FAMOUS.

13:32.445 --> 13:34.747
AND WHAT
DID YOU GET?

13:34.814 --> 13:35.983
A CHIP
ON YOUR SHOULDER

13:36.049 --> 13:39.052
THE SIZE
OF AN AIRCRAFT
CARRIER.

13:43.023 --> 13:44.424
WHAT ARE YOU SAYING,
GUMSHOE?

13:44.491 --> 13:46.693
I'M SAYING
YOU KILLED
YOUR OWN SISTER!

13:46.759 --> 13:48.461
[THUNDER]

13:48.528 --> 13:50.230
[GUNSHOT]

13:54.101 --> 13:57.204
ON SECOND THOUGHT,
IT WASN'T HARRIETTE.

14:02.742 --> 14:04.244
WAS IT, EDDIE?

14:04.311 --> 14:05.645
UH, WHAT?

14:05.712 --> 14:06.880
THAT'S RIGHT.

14:06.947 --> 14:08.381
YOU WERE
RUNNING NUMBERS,

14:08.448 --> 14:11.151
AND RACHEL FOUND OUT
ABOUT IT, DIDN'T SHE?

14:13.820 --> 14:16.089
I WAS DOING
ALL THE WORK,

14:16.156 --> 14:18.926
AND SHE WANTED 80%.
IT WASN'T FAIR.

14:18.992 --> 14:21.995
NO, IT WASN'T,
BUT YOU DIDN'T
HAVE TO KILL HER!

14:22.062 --> 14:23.630
[THUNDER]

14:23.696 --> 14:25.532
[GUNSHOT]

14:34.007 --> 14:36.576
AND WHICH, OF COURSE,
YOU DIDN'T.

14:39.246 --> 14:44.217
WAIT A MINUTE.
EVERY TIME HE ACCUSES
SOMEBODY, THEY DIE.

14:44.284 --> 14:46.186
WHICH BRINGS ME
TO YOU.

14:46.253 --> 14:47.220
NO!

14:54.161 --> 14:57.197
NOT SO FAST,
FLATFOOT.

14:57.264 --> 14:59.899
YOU'RE GOING TO MAKE
HEADLINES AGAIN.

14:59.967 --> 15:01.134
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

15:01.201 --> 15:02.335
YOU WERE BEING INVESTIGATED

15:02.402 --> 15:05.305
FOR RUNNING A CITYWIDE
EXTORTION SCHEME.

15:05.372 --> 15:09.576
IF A BUSINESS DIDN'T PAY,
THEY MET WITH AN ACCIDENT.

15:09.642 --> 15:10.978
RACHEL WAS
MAKING MILLIONS.

15:11.044 --> 15:13.480
IT WOULDN'T
HAVE KILLED HER
TO SHARE THE WEALTH.

15:13.546 --> 15:16.383
YOU KILLED HER
BECAUSE SHE DIDN'T
SHARE THE WEALTH!

15:16.449 --> 15:18.285
[THUNDER]

15:18.351 --> 15:19.619
[GUNSHOT]

15:23.390 --> 15:24.691
YOU KNOW..

15:27.227 --> 15:28.561
WHOEVER'S DOING THIS

15:28.628 --> 15:32.632
JUST MIGHT WANT TO WAIT
UNTIL I'M FINISHED.

15:32.699 --> 15:34.334
THIS IS CRAZY!

15:34.401 --> 15:36.103
[DRUMS BEATING]

15:37.170 --> 15:39.006
LAURA! SIT BACK DOWN.

15:39.072 --> 15:42.042
I CAN'T THINK
WITH THOSE DRUMS.

15:51.418 --> 15:52.585
ESTELLE.

15:52.652 --> 15:53.620
YES, SUGAR?

15:56.056 --> 15:59.092
YOU MENTIONED EARLIER
THAT RACHEL WAS LOVED.

15:59.159 --> 16:00.660
DID YOU LOVE HER?

16:00.727 --> 16:02.562
NO, I DIDN'T.

16:02.629 --> 16:03.830
RACHEL WAS A HUSSY.

16:03.896 --> 16:05.965
SHE STOLE MY MAN.

16:06.033 --> 16:08.201
- JUDGE JENKINS?
- THAT'S RIGHT.

16:08.268 --> 16:11.638
AND SHE CONVINCED
HIM TO PUT ME
IN A REST HOME.

16:18.945 --> 16:21.381
AH, I SEE.

16:21.448 --> 16:24.751
SO NOT ONLY WOULD RACHEL
HAVE YOUR MAN,

16:24.817 --> 16:26.519
BUT SHE WOULD
HAVE YOUR MONEY.

16:26.586 --> 16:30.423
NOW LISTEN, I ADMIT I HAD
HARSH WORDS WITH RACHEL,

16:30.490 --> 16:33.193
BUT I SWEAR
I DIDN'T KILL HER.

16:33.260 --> 16:35.928
I DIDN'T KILL HER!

16:35.995 --> 16:37.830
OH, ESTELLE...

16:37.897 --> 16:40.100
IF WE COULD
ONLY BELIEVE YOU.

16:40.167 --> 16:41.801
[THUNDER]

16:41.868 --> 16:43.336
[GUNSHOT]

16:47.907 --> 16:50.477
AND WE DO BELIEVE
YOU, ESTELLE.

16:50.543 --> 16:53.413
WE REALLY DO.

16:55.715 --> 16:58.085
CHEF WALDO..

16:58.151 --> 17:00.053
TELL ME...

17:00.120 --> 17:03.323
DOES THIS CONTRACT
LOOK FAMILIAR TO YOU?

17:09.696 --> 17:12.599
YEAH. I SIGN IT WHEN RACHEL
BRING ME TO AMERICA.

17:15.268 --> 17:17.204
WERE YOU AWARE
WHEN YOU SIGNED IT

17:17.270 --> 17:19.972
THAT IT WAS
A LIFETIME CONTRACT?

17:20.039 --> 17:23.076
NO! FOR SEVEN LONG YEARS,

17:23.143 --> 17:26.613
I BASTE, I STUFF,
AND I FRICASSEE FOR HER.

17:26.679 --> 17:28.115
AND I ASK HER,

17:28.181 --> 17:33.052
LETTA ME START
ME OWN RISTORANTE.
BUT SHE SAY NO!

17:34.954 --> 17:38.391
YOU HAVE A LITTLE
DROOL RIGHT HERE.

17:41.194 --> 17:43.396
OH. THANK YOU
VERY MUCH.

17:44.897 --> 17:49.102
SO, RACHEL DESTROYED
YOUR DREAM,

17:49.169 --> 17:52.004
AND THATSA WHY
YOU KILLED HER.

17:52.071 --> 17:53.606
[THUNDER]

17:53.673 --> 17:55.308
[GUNSHOT]

18:00.647 --> 18:03.650
GEE. I WOULD'VE
BET MONEY
ON THAT ONE.

18:05.618 --> 18:07.387
SO...

18:11.291 --> 18:15.495
WIGGLESWORTH, IT ALL
COMES DOWN TO YOU.

18:15.562 --> 18:17.630
HA. I DIDN'T
KILL ANYBODY.

18:17.697 --> 18:19.098
OH, REALLY?

18:19.166 --> 18:20.467
MURTAGH ORDERED YOU

18:20.533 --> 18:22.669
TO COLLECT THE EXTORTION
MONEY FROM RACHEL.

18:22.735 --> 18:25.572
NOT ONLY DID SHE REFUSE,

18:25.638 --> 18:28.475
SHE SHOWED YOU THIS!

18:34.046 --> 18:35.182
WHAT'S THAT?

18:35.248 --> 18:36.683
RACHEL
SECRETLY RECORDED

18:36.749 --> 18:38.651
YOUR FATHER'S
DEMAND FOR MONEY.

18:38.718 --> 18:42.121
ISN'T THAT RIGHT,
OFFICER WIGGLESWORTH?

18:42.189 --> 18:45.091
WELL, SHE WAS GOING
TO LEAK IT TO THE PRESS.

18:45.158 --> 18:46.759
MY CAREER
WOULD'VE BEEN RUINED.

18:46.826 --> 18:48.228
AND SO
YOU KILLED HER!

18:48.295 --> 18:50.163
[THUNDER]

18:50.230 --> 18:51.231
NO!

18:51.298 --> 18:53.132
[GUNSHOT]

18:56.936 --> 18:59.572
LAURA,
I KNEW IT WAS YOU!

19:01.941 --> 19:06.346
YOU DID?
THEN WHY'D YOU LET ME
SHOOT ALL THESE PEOPLE?

19:06.413 --> 19:09.382
I WANTED TO MAKE YOU
SWEAT A LITTLE.

19:10.850 --> 19:13.586
WELL, NOW IT'S YOUR TURN,
JOHNNY DANGER.

19:13.653 --> 19:15.788
YOUR TURN TO DIE.

19:15.855 --> 19:19.526
THERE I WAS, FACE TO FACE
WITH LADY DEATH.

19:19.592 --> 19:22.195
WAS I ABOUT
TO TAKE THE LONG NAP,

19:22.262 --> 19:24.030
THE SIESTA GRANDE,

19:24.096 --> 19:25.932
THE ETERNAL SNOOZE,

19:25.998 --> 19:28.735
THE HASTA LA BYE-BYE?

19:30.069 --> 19:32.004
WELL, WHAT ARE YOU
WAITING FOR?

19:32.071 --> 19:34.407
THE NARRATION TO FINISH.

19:43.783 --> 19:45.785
YOU'RE A STRONG WOMAN.

19:47.520 --> 19:49.489
ALRIGHT, JOHNNY,
YOU'VE GOT ME.

19:49.556 --> 19:50.957
I KILLED
MY AUNT RACHEL.

19:51.023 --> 19:52.592
BUT WHY?

19:52.659 --> 19:54.427
[DRUMS BEATING]

19:59.799 --> 20:01.634
I WANTED TO INHERIT
THE SUPPER CLUB.

20:01.701 --> 20:03.470
I KILLED THE REST
OF THE FAMILY

20:03.536 --> 20:05.772
BECAUSE I WAS
LAST IN LINE.

20:06.973 --> 20:08.741
OH...

20:08.808 --> 20:11.811
OH, YOU'RE COLD, BABY.

20:11.878 --> 20:14.414
COLD...AND IRRESISTIBLE.

20:16.182 --> 20:17.384
WHAT ARE YOU SAYING?

20:17.450 --> 20:20.387
I'M SAYING I'M CRAZY
ABOUT YOU, KID.

20:20.453 --> 20:21.888
YOU'RE UNDER MY SKIN.

20:21.954 --> 20:24.156
I KNOW YOU'RE POISON,
BUT I'VE BEEN BITTEN,

20:24.223 --> 20:27.460
AND I DON'T
HAVE AN ANTIDOTE.

20:28.795 --> 20:32.399
SO...YOU'RE GOING
TO LET ME GO?

20:32.465 --> 20:34.701
I'M GIVING YOU
A CHOICE.

20:34.767 --> 20:35.802
WE CAN RUN AWAY

20:35.868 --> 20:38.805
AND SPEND THE REST
OF OUR LIVES
TOGETHER...

20:38.871 --> 20:40.172
OR...

20:40.239 --> 20:42.409
YOU CAN GO TO JAIL.

20:49.849 --> 20:51.418
CHICAGO POLICE?

20:53.620 --> 20:55.888
I'VE JUST KILLED
SEVEN PEOPLE.

21:04.030 --> 21:05.932
AND SO...

21:05.998 --> 21:07.166
IT ENDED.

21:07.233 --> 21:09.469
THE COPS
TOOK LAURA AWAY,

21:09.536 --> 21:11.571
AND I NEVER SAW HER AGAIN.

21:11.638 --> 21:14.841
BUT EVERY TIME THE CARDS
PLAY THE BOSOX,

21:14.907 --> 21:18.244
I BOW MY HEAD
AND SHED A TEAR

21:18.311 --> 21:22.081
FOR THE LOVELY
LAURA WIGGLESWORTH.

21:22.148 --> 21:25.485
SO, LADIES,
WHAT DID YOU THINK?

21:25.552 --> 21:27.554
- ACTUALLY, I LIKED IT.
- SO DID I.

21:27.620 --> 21:30.222
I HOPE YOU WIN
THAT WRITING CONTEST.

21:30.289 --> 21:32.659
COME ON, YOU TWO, IT'S LATE.
LET'S GO HOME.

21:36.262 --> 21:39.432
* I'M JUST
AN UNLUCKY STAR *

21:39.499 --> 21:42.702
* AN UNLUCKY STAR *

21:43.536 --> 21:46.639
STEVE,
YOU WROTE THE STORY.

21:46.706 --> 21:49.742
WHY DIDN'T YOU HAVE JOHNNY
END UP WITH LAURA?

21:49.809 --> 21:50.877
WELL...

21:50.943 --> 21:52.379
SIMPLE, SWEETHEART.

21:52.445 --> 21:55.448
I'M SAVING THAT ENDING
FOR REAL LIFE.
